  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Author of a funeral epigram from the ‘Garland’ 
    of Meleager, dedicated to the poet Phaenocritus (the name is otherwise unknown) of Ialysus
    (Anth. Pal. 7,716). This D. (the name is too common to allow definite identifications)
    could also be the author of the ‘Meleagrian’ poems 6,3, 7,462
    12,108, simply entitled Διονυσίου Dionysíou..." Degani, Enzo (Bologna). Dionysius." 
    Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online.</mads:note>  
